data-triple-N3.o: "Henan is a province of the People's Republic of China, located in the central part of the country. Its one-character abbreviation is "豫" (yu), named after Yuzhou (豫州 Yu Zhou), a Han Dynasty state that included parts of Henan. Although the name of the province (河南) means "south of the river", approximately a quarter of the province lies north of the Yellow River, also known as the "Huang He"."@en
